1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,460
A box lands on the counter, fifty tubes of the cream.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:09,280
The one that's been selling, the driver wants a signature, fifty units, he says, count them.

3
00:00:09,980 --> 00:00:16,100
On an old tilt, this is the worst job in the shop. You count all fifty. You match them to the order.

4
00:00:16,420 --> 00:00:20,720
One's missing, recount. The driver's tapping his foot. The line's back,

5
00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:27,520
keen up. And heaven help you if you're off by one because now the whole system is lying.

6
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:35,840
Ralph doesn't count. He scans one tube just to say this arrived and he's done.

7
00:00:36,620 --> 00:00:42,680
The box is in. He never typed a quantity because here's the thing nobody tells you.

8
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:48,240
Banko doesn't track how many you have. It tracks what you sell.

9
00:00:49,160 --> 00:00:55,420
The shelf isn't a number in a database. It's the real shelf in the real shop.

10
00:00:55,420 --> 00:01:02,420
And that's slip. The one that says five trays. That's not a stock count.

11
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:08,580
That's how many labels to print. Five creams, five trays, five labels.

12
00:01:09,580 --> 00:01:15,640
The number on the paper was never about inventory. It was about getting price tags on the shelf.

13
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:22,620
What about the money? The box costs 120 francs for fifty.

14
00:01:22,620 --> 00:01:28,340
Banko does the math. That's your cost per tube baked right in.

15
00:01:28,540 --> 00:01:36,000
You bought a box. It splits into singles. The margins already there before the first one sells.

16
00:01:36,580 --> 00:01:40,960
So the delivery that used to eat twenty minutes and start an argument.

17
00:01:41,380 --> 00:01:46,300
Ralph logged that. It came and walked away. No count.

18
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:53,580
No reconcile. No clipboard. Dock to drawer. And nobody counted the thing.

19
00:01:53,820 --> 00:01:58,080
Because you don't count a shop in. You sell it down.

20
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:02,300
The cream came in quiet. And now it's back on the shelf.

21
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:08,000
Waiting for Larry, and Sally — and whoever's next.
